article.description: Eastern Kentucky holds off Jacksonville St. 60-56
article.headline: Eastern Kentucky holds off Jacksonville St. 60-56
article.linkText: Eastern Kentucky holds off Jacksonville St. 60-56
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Eric Stutz scored 14 of his 20 points in the second half, and grabbed nine rebounds, to lead Eastern Kentucky past Jacksonville State 60-56 Saturday night. Glenn Cosey, who finished with 17 points and made 11 of 12 free-throw attempts, hit a pair from the line with 4 seconds to play -- giving Eastern Kentucky (13-6, 4-2 Ohio Valley) a 60-56 lead and, essentially, icing the game. Undra Mitchem's layup with just over 8 minutes to play gave Jacksonville State (9-13, 3-4) a 42-40 advantage, but Stutz scored eight points in the final 7:40 and EKU made 11 of 12 free throws down the stretch. Tarius Johnson scored 12 points and made 3 of 4 from 3-point range for the Colonels. Brian Williams scored 16 points and had six assists to lead JSU. Darion Rackley added 12 points.
